article.description: — Alex Arians scored 19 points and led five players in double-digit scoring as South Dakota State rolled over Denver, 80-62 on Saturday to stay unbeaten through six Summit League games.
article.headline: Arians leads South Dakota State in romp past Denver, 80-62
article.linkText: Arians leads South Dakota State in romp past Denver, 80-62
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- — Alex Arians scored 19 points and led five players in double-digit scoring as South Dakota State rolled over Denver, 80-62 on Saturday to stay unbeaten through six Summit League games. The Jackrabbits raced to a 21-point lead at intermission, 44-23, and cruised to the win. Luke Appel scored 12 points and grabbed seven rebounds off the bench, D Wilson and B Scheierman each added 11 points and M Mims contributed 10 points for South Dakota State (15-4, 6-0 Summit League). K.J. Hunt scored 18 points to lead Denver (6-14, 2-5). Coban Porter added 16 point off the bench and Touko Tainamo added 13 points and six rebounds. ------ https://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/boxscore/--/gameId/401371139 AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP--Top25
